The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, Aug. 31: The rate of inflation declined to below 4 per cent for the first time in more than 15 months to touch 3.94 per cent for the week ended August 18, much less than the Reserve Banks projection for this fiscal. Before this week, inflation was below this level only during the week ended April 29, 2006. Wholesale prices-based inflation is now way below the RBIs projection of around 5 per cent this fiscal.

 London, Aug. 31: Fiat is planning to join hands with the Tatas in the latters bid to acquire Ford Motors British brands Jaguar and Land Rover, an Italian newspaper reported today. The companies already have a partnership under which Tata Motors distributes Fiats vehicles.

 New Delhi, Aug. 31: The Centres revenue deficit stood at Rs 82,400 crore in the first four months of 2007-08, exceeding the estimates for the entire fiscal. This implies that the governments expenditure on the revenue account is growing at a faster rate than its revenue receipts, including taxes.

 New Delhi, Aug. 31: The department of telecom (DoT) today sought stakeholders views on the proposed changes in the current spectrum allocation, usage and pricing norms.

 Mumbai, Aug. 31: Pantaloon Retail India will seek shareholders approval to invest Rs 325 crore in its subsidiary Pantaloon Future Ventures.

 Calcutta, Aug. 31: Balrampur Chini Mills has acquired 53.96 per cent of Indo Gulf Industries after settlement of shares under dispute, which represents 6 per cent of Indo Gulf.

 New Delhi, Aug. 31: Rahul Bajaj failed to settle with his brother Shishir the division of the Bajaj group within the time allotted by the Company Law Board (CLB). The brothers today sought some more time from the principal bench of the CLB.




